Scramble! prototype ... 
(http://tinyurl.com/scrambleIt)  

License: EPL
Authors: COSIC, K.U.Leuven (filipe.beato@esat.kuleuven.be)


USER MODE:
  Installation:
   1. If not installed, install Mozilla Firefox
   2. If not installed, install GnuPG
   3. Open the scramble.xpi file with Firefox
   4. Use the Initialisation dialog (run for first installation) to configure the main preferences
   5. Run Settings dialog to change any extra settings
   6. Scramble! is up and running... 


DEVELOPER MODE:

  Installation:
	- Open the XPI file with Firefox
	(see requirements on README)
	- If developer wants to perform changes and install in the debug mode:
		. Extract to a folder (EXT_FOLDER)
		. Go to the <Firefox/Profiles/CurrentProfile/extentions> 
		. Create a file name "scramble@primelife.net" and copy the PATH_To_EXT_FOLDER to the first line of the file

  Build XPI file:
	- Run the script file 'build.sh' available in scr/ folder
	- The latest XPI file will be present in package/ folder

